WEBVTT

00:13.722 --> 00:14.723
God.

01:09.778 --> 01:11.196
Thought we were gonna see the widow?

01:11.697 --> 01:12.698
We are.

01:13.782 --> 01:16.076
We're just gonna have a word
with her sisters first.

01:33.427 --> 01:34.428
Oh, fuck.

01:36.889 --> 01:37.890
Oh, shit.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.853
Shit. Fuck.

01:52.988 --> 01:54.948
You know,
they have every right not to talk to us.

01:55.032 --> 01:56.491
You know that, right? We're not Garda.

01:56.575 --> 01:58.994
Absolutely.
I think they shouldn't talk to us.

01:59.077 --> 02:00.370
What? Well, then, why are we here?

02:00.454 --> 02:02.915
If they don't answer our questions,
we'll leave them alone,

02:02.998 --> 02:04.458
admit defeat, pay out.

02:04.541 --> 02:08.628
But if they invite us in,
we'll know they've got something to hide.

02:08.711 --> 02:12.799
And then we'll haul each one of them
over hot coals until we get to the truth.

02:14.176 --> 02:16.929
Sorry to bother.
Thomas Claffin, Claffin and Sons.

02:18.472 --> 02:19.473
Yeah, I remember you.

02:22.976 --> 02:24.061
Come in.

03:42.472 --> 03:44.391
Do you mind if I record our conversation?

03:44.933 --> 03:45.934
What for?

03:46.018 --> 03:49.146
It's mostly just for,
you know, so I have it--

03:49.229 --> 03:51.481
It's fine. Go ahead.

03:52.232 --> 03:53.483
Do your thing.

03:54.067 --> 03:55.068
Great.

04:00.908 --> 04:04.203
Miss Garvey,
do you mind telling us where you were

04:04.286 --> 04:07.831
the night of claim reference 1757318?

04:08.790 --> 04:10.167
The night Mr. Williams died.

04:10.834 --> 04:14.838
Do you mind telling me what my whereabouts
has to do with our claim?

04:14.922 --> 04:18.091
When we're dealing with
a payout of this size, it's customary to--

04:18.175 --> 04:19.927
Yeah, it's okay. I was with Grace.

04:20.427 --> 04:21.428
We all were.

04:22.679 --> 04:24.723
-All of you?
-Yeah.

04:24.806 --> 04:25.807
Yeah, we're very close.

04:25.891 --> 04:27.726
We get together as often as we can here.

04:27.809 --> 04:28.936
Well, that's nice.

04:29.019 --> 04:30.646
Tight-knit family.

04:30.729 --> 04:33.899
I mean, I didn't even meet my brother
till he was about, what, five years old.

04:33.982 --> 04:36.652
-Let's just stay on track.
-This is your brother?

04:37.152 --> 04:38.862
-Thought he was your son.
-No.

04:40.280 --> 04:41.281
How would he be my son?

04:41.365 --> 04:44.826
-Well, just, it's Claffin and Sons.
-No, that's our father.

04:44.910 --> 04:45.953
Yeah. Also, I'm 35.

04:46.036 --> 04:47.120
We're half brothers.

04:47.204 --> 04:48.914
Yeah? No shit.

04:50.916 --> 04:55.379
You and the insured, Mr. Williams,
you were colleagues?

04:55.963 --> 04:56.964
Yeah.

04:57.965 --> 04:58.966
Were you very close?

05:01.385 --> 05:04.179
We weren't very close.
No. We didn't get on.

05:04.763 --> 05:06.181
Meaning?

05:06.265 --> 05:08.350
Meaning you don't get to choose
your brother-in-law.

05:10.143 --> 05:11.144
Right.

05:12.437 --> 05:15.190
And you didn't think
that he was good enough for her or--

05:26.076 --> 05:28.245
Sorry. It's a friend.

05:28.829 --> 05:29.788
Friend.

05:30.372 --> 05:32.583
Hi, this is Matt. Leave a message.

05:34.960 --> 05:36.545
Very seductive.

05:36.628 --> 05:39.131
You should
save something for the imagination.

05:39.214 --> 05:40.591
A girl likes a little mystery.

05:42.384 --> 05:44.761
So, Matt, I have a free night,

05:44.845 --> 05:49.057
and I was wondering
if you maybe wanted to grab some dinner.

05:50.434 --> 05:54.646
This is Becka, by the way.
From the pub. From the accident.

05:55.814 --> 05:57.316
I said I'd massage you.

05:59.193 --> 06:00.194
Oh, shit.

06:00.277 --> 06:02.529
Not in a sexual way. It's--

06:03.363 --> 06:05.032
Hello? Oh, shit.

06:05.949 --> 06:06.950
Okay.

06:10.078 --> 06:11.788
Now, the night the AD&D came into effect…

06:11.872 --> 06:13.832
-That's accidental--
-Yeah, I get it. Yeah.

06:13.916 --> 06:16.752
…do you remember anything
out of the ordinary?

06:17.836 --> 06:20.339
Any odd behavior from the decedent?

06:21.089 --> 06:22.925
-Do you mean John Paul?
-Yeah.

06:23.008 --> 06:24.384
Just say that then.

06:25.260 --> 06:28.263
Anything at work that may have
spilt over into your personal lives?

06:29.556 --> 06:31.350
A quarrel perhaps?

06:31.433 --> 06:34.186
Anything strange that night?

06:35.604 --> 06:37.314
Well, there was something strange.

06:38.273 --> 06:40.234
Actually, yeah, now that you mention it.

06:42.110 --> 06:43.403
The weather was really bad.

06:44.530 --> 06:47.199
I remember a tree had come down
along the main road.

06:47.282 --> 06:48.283
And…

06:50.077 --> 06:51.662
-And go on.
-Well--

06:51.745 --> 06:54.831
Well, we were ordering in
from a Chinese restaurant,

06:54.915 --> 06:58.377
but 20 minutes later,
there's a bang on the door.

06:59.253 --> 07:00.379
And?

07:01.672 --> 07:03.924
And he hands over a bag of Mexican food.

07:05.551 --> 07:06.802
From a Chinese restaurant.

07:07.386 --> 07:08.887
Like, a bunch of Mexican food.

07:11.056 --> 07:12.057
Isn't that weird?

07:13.725 --> 07:15.477
I thought that was weird.

07:26.989 --> 07:28.031
Drive safe.

07:31.076 --> 07:34.204
-Well, you can see why she's alone.
-Didn't give us much, did she?

07:35.330 --> 07:36.331
She gave us plenty.

07:37.249 --> 07:40.043
The cheeky remarks. The deflection.

07:41.253 --> 07:44.339
-Something she didn't want to answer.
-It was you. She didn't wanna answer you.

07:44.423 --> 07:46.800
I don't know.
I thought I was fairly charming.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.304
Bit early for a fire.

07:50.387 --> 07:53.765
Yeah. Clearly the godmother
of the murderous middle-aged sister gang

07:53.849 --> 07:55.017
is burning evidence.

07:55.100 --> 07:57.060
-Still a joke to you, is it?
-No.

07:57.144 --> 07:59.897
But there's no evidence a crime was
committed. We should be looking for fraud.

07:59.980 --> 08:02.691
Murder is fraud
when there's a life policy to pay out.

08:03.817 --> 08:05.736
-Trust me. I've seen this before.
-When?

08:05.819 --> 08:06.862
Get in the car.

08:10.282 --> 08:13.410
-So, what now?
-Yeah. I've been thinking about this.

08:14.536 --> 08:15.829
We need to exhume the body.

08:16.496 --> 08:17.664
Exhume the-- W--

08:17.748 --> 08:19.499
When you say "we," do you mean you and I?

08:19.583 --> 08:21.001
No. The coroner.

08:21.084 --> 08:22.669
There was no postmortem.

08:22.753 --> 08:24.046
Who knows what we find.

08:24.129 --> 08:27.299
Fingerprints. Needle marks.
Maybe there was drugs in his system.

08:27.382 --> 08:28.383
You've lost your mind.

08:28.467 --> 08:30.093
It's better
than losing my bloody business,

08:30.177 --> 08:31.887
which will happen if we don't prove

08:31.970 --> 08:34.640
-that this man was murdered. Thank you.
-Murdered.

08:53.408 --> 08:54.868
-What are you doing?
-Hang on.

08:56.161 --> 08:57.412
What, Tom?

09:08.841 --> 09:09.842
What are you doing?

09:10.676 --> 09:11.927
Evidence, Matthew.

09:13.804 --> 09:15.347
What the fuck?

09:56.096 --> 09:58.390
Bye, Dad! I'll see you after school!

10:04.313 --> 10:05.480
Gracie!

10:06.064 --> 10:09.902
Need to get into work! It's quarter to!

10:09.985 --> 10:11.486
Five seconds!

10:13.155 --> 10:15.866
-Two seconds!
-All right.

10:19.828 --> 10:20.829
Lovely.

10:21.747 --> 10:25.167
I'm going to have a steam
after the gym, so let's eat at 8:00.

10:25.250 --> 10:28.921
I have a stiff calf
I need some moist heat on.

10:29.004 --> 10:30.964
Good idea. Get ready for the walk.

10:31.048 --> 10:34.760
It's not a walk.
It's a 15K all-terrain elite hike.

10:34.843 --> 10:37.763
Which by the way, none of your sisters
have sponsored me for.

10:37.846 --> 10:39.431
They're probably just busy.

10:39.515 --> 10:43.018
Break these in for me, will you?
Just wear them around the house.

10:44.394 --> 10:46.563
And go to the salon while you're in town.

10:46.855 --> 10:48.106
Treat yourself to a freshen up.

10:49.441 --> 10:50.817
You think I need a freshen up?

10:50.901 --> 10:52.694
Did I say "need"?

10:54.112 --> 10:55.364
Thought I said "treat."

10:56.490 --> 11:01.119
Gracie, honestly,
don't make me walk on glass.

11:22.683 --> 11:23.851
What?

11:24.560 --> 11:26.728
I just learned so much about you.

11:27.896 --> 11:31.066
Wow! You're a completely different person
than I thought.

11:31.149 --> 11:32.901
-Really?
-Yeah.

11:33.610 --> 11:34.987
What did you think I was like?

11:35.487 --> 11:39.867
I don't know. Thought you'd
be more classic, like Céline Dion, Cher.

11:41.076 --> 11:42.244
Fuck off.

11:45.247 --> 11:47.583
Fucking Céline Dion?

11:54.673 --> 11:56.008
Architecture is God?

11:57.050 --> 12:01.054
Oh, no, I bless myself because I
so desperately want that not to get built.

12:02.431 --> 12:03.682
I like it.

12:03.765 --> 12:05.392
Why? You not a fan of change?

12:07.477 --> 12:09.104
What? You like it?

12:09.897 --> 12:11.023
Yeah, I'm a fan of change.

12:11.106 --> 12:13.775
I mean, normally I love what we do,
but that's just…

12:14.610 --> 12:16.612
Look at that. That is a street crime.

12:18.197 --> 12:19.489
And it's gonna bankrupt us.

12:20.616 --> 12:23.619
A little bird told me
you're about to be financial director.

12:24.328 --> 12:25.370
Maybe.

12:25.454 --> 12:28.373
Who do I have to sleep with
to get an opportunity like that?

12:28.874 --> 12:30.834
-Me.
-What?

12:30.918 --> 12:32.044
What do you mean? What?

12:32.127 --> 12:33.754
-No, I was just--
-No, I was joking.

12:33.837 --> 12:35.881
I-- Lost in translation. I--

12:36.381 --> 12:38.675
Gerald! You'd have to sleep with Gerald.

12:39.676 --> 12:41.845
-Well, I'm pleased.
-What's he doing in?

12:42.554 --> 12:44.097
He's never normally here this early.

12:44.181 --> 12:46.850
Yeah. Maybe he's filing a complaint
against himself.

12:46.934 --> 12:47.935
Morning, team.

12:49.520 --> 12:51.522
Gabriel, we never really had
a chance to talk.

12:51.605 --> 12:53.148
How are you settling in? All good?

12:53.232 --> 12:54.358
Yes, great, thank you.

12:54.858 --> 12:56.610
But we've met and talked several times.

12:56.693 --> 12:57.694
Obvi-- Yes, of course.

12:57.778 --> 13:00.572
But anything I can do to help
to give you the smoothest entry possible,

13:00.656 --> 13:01.657
just say.

13:01.740 --> 13:03.617
-Jesus Christ.
-Eva?

13:03.700 --> 13:06.161
I just put my hat in the ring
for the financial director post.

13:07.246 --> 13:08.539
Gerald's pleased, of course.

13:08.997 --> 13:11.542
So I hope you don't mind
a little friendly competition

13:12.209 --> 13:14.878
from the one person here
who knows your dirty secrets.

13:15.963 --> 13:16.964
Just joking.

13:19.716 --> 13:20.843
What?

13:34.231 --> 13:37.651
I have to go home. I have to get there
before Donal and the kids get back.

13:38.277 --> 13:39.862
What are you doing?

13:41.071 --> 13:42.406
Hold on.

13:42.489 --> 13:44.032
What are you do-- I said I had to go.

13:44.116 --> 13:47.035
-Hang on, are you writing on me?
-Just hold still.

13:48.328 --> 13:51.081
That really tickles. Okay.

13:59.298 --> 14:01.091
Why would you do something so stupid?

14:03.010 --> 14:04.219
I don't know.

14:04.303 --> 14:06.680
Maybe being with you
makes me do stupid things.

14:16.607 --> 14:20.068
-I feel like I've run 10K.
-I could go another right now.

14:21.862 --> 14:24.364
So, will I get to see you tomorrow?

14:24.448 --> 14:26.283
Yeah, I hope so.
As long as I get back before--

14:26.366 --> 14:29.036
Oh, for fuck's sake.
It's my brother-in-law. He's a prick.

14:29.119 --> 14:30.370
Hi, JP.

14:30.454 --> 14:32.414
-You're a long way from home.
-Yeah.

14:34.791 --> 14:36.376
You gonna introduce us?

14:36.877 --> 14:39.505
Yeah, of course. It's-- This is Ben.

14:40.422 --> 14:41.882
He's my photography teacher.

14:43.550 --> 14:44.760
I just had a class.

14:45.177 --> 14:48.222
We all need our outlets, don't we?
Keeps life from getting stale.

14:48.931 --> 14:50.140
How's she getting on?

14:50.390 --> 14:52.100
Yeah. She's great.

14:52.809 --> 14:53.810
She's a talent.

14:53.894 --> 14:55.354
I'm sure she is.

14:56.271 --> 14:58.440
Well, back to class.

15:05.614 --> 15:07.866
Here we go. Home again.

15:07.950 --> 15:09.826
Thanks for taking me shopping, Auntie Eva.

15:09.910 --> 15:11.036
You coming in?

15:11.411 --> 15:15.666
-No. I've a stack of work on, so…
-All right. Bye.

15:15.749 --> 15:17.000
-Hey!
-Hey.

15:17.084 --> 15:18.085
Come in!

15:18.502 --> 15:19.795
Please.

15:19.878 --> 15:21.922
Fuck's sake. Okay.

15:23.632 --> 15:24.633
Okay.

15:26.009 --> 15:28.011
I don't know if that would be enough.

15:28.762 --> 15:30.597
Do it! Do the drop. Do the--

15:30.681 --> 15:32.683
-Oh, God!
-Wow.

15:32.766 --> 15:34.017
Then, whoa.

15:36.395 --> 15:37.855
You can do it. You do it.

15:37.938 --> 15:39.231
You got the moves.

15:39.731 --> 15:40.983
Another bag of goodies?

15:41.066 --> 15:43.110
Yeah, well. That's what aunties are for.

15:43.193 --> 15:45.195
Not all aunties.
Do you remember Auntie Orla?

15:45.279 --> 15:47.906
Is this a terrible thing to say?
Is she dead?

15:47.990 --> 15:50.033
Yes, Eva. She is dead.

15:50.117 --> 15:52.619
But it's hard to remember it
'cause she was ill for so long.

15:52.703 --> 15:53.996
And then she got better.

15:54.079 --> 15:55.831
And then she disappeared.

16:00.085 --> 16:02.087
I was gonna say.
Lizzo's playing in Dublin next week.

16:02.171 --> 16:03.714
Birthday present for the Blanaid?

16:03.797 --> 16:05.340
-Over my dead body.
-Yes.

16:05.424 --> 16:06.425
-Hey.
-Hey.

16:08.010 --> 16:09.678
Eva, to what do we owe the pleasure?

16:10.512 --> 16:12.055
I was just dropping Blanaid back.

16:12.139 --> 16:14.057
Do you know what? I should head off now.

16:14.141 --> 16:15.767
How was school, sweetheart?

16:15.851 --> 16:17.728
Did you get your mark back
on your photosynthesis quiz?

16:17.811 --> 16:18.937
Got a 96.

16:19.646 --> 16:20.772
An A-star.

16:21.398 --> 16:22.399
That's great!

16:23.817 --> 16:27.070
-It's not from the ground she licked it.
-Will you not stay for dinner, no?

16:27.154 --> 16:29.364
Oh, no.
You know, I've got a stack of work on--

16:29.448 --> 16:32.075
What is it they say?
To be a perfect guest, stay at home.

16:32.159 --> 16:34.786
Mammy, we need to get this soaking.

16:34.870 --> 16:36.455
Otherwise you're looking at a stain.

16:41.168 --> 16:42.920
I have not had to put the bins out
in ten years.

16:43.003 --> 16:45.756
-Did I say a thing? I didn't say a thing.
-No, it's just…

16:48.258 --> 16:49.426
-Hey.
-Hey.

16:49.510 --> 16:51.094
I'll see you later, chicken.

16:51.178 --> 16:54.765
Come here. Why'd you stop dancing
when your daddy walked in?

16:54.848 --> 16:56.683
He just doesn't like it
when I dance like that.

16:56.767 --> 16:57.893
Huh? What?

16:58.393 --> 17:00.729
Yeah, he says
it looks like I'm asking for it.

17:05.483 --> 17:07.528
The prick's becoming an even bigger prick.

17:08.111 --> 17:10.614
He put himself up for the promotion today.
My promotion.

17:11.114 --> 17:12.782
He's doing it to mess with my head, but--

17:12.866 --> 17:15.327
I've been thinking about
that talk we had a while back.

17:15.827 --> 17:17.204
What talk?

17:17.287 --> 17:19.873
Christmas. At the Forty Foot.

17:19.957 --> 17:22.792
Yeah, I was pissed, Bibi.
You're gonna have to remind me.

17:22.876 --> 17:24.294
About looking out for Grace.

17:24.795 --> 17:26.421
-Oh, right, yeah.
-And killing John Paul.

17:29.174 --> 17:30.300
What?

17:30.384 --> 17:31.677
It's all I think about.

17:32.719 --> 17:34.263
It's on a loop in my head.

17:34.346 --> 17:36.223
What are you talking about, Bibi?

17:36.932 --> 17:39.601
-We were joking!
-Well, I wasn't.

17:39.685 --> 17:41.228
Well, I was!

17:41.311 --> 17:44.356
Eva, you said so yourself.
He's sucking the life out of her.

17:44.439 --> 17:47.526
-He's slowly killing her.
-I'm hungry. Are you a bit hungry?

17:47.609 --> 17:51.363
Eva, we cannot just sit back
and do nothing while he drags her under.

17:52.114 --> 17:54.408
God knows, she's not gonna save herself.

17:54.491 --> 17:56.743
I'm not sure what I have.
I might order in though.

17:56.827 --> 17:58.203
Imagine being rid of him.

17:58.620 --> 18:01.999
The prick, gone from her life.
Gone from all of our lives.

18:03.250 --> 18:05.335
I've been thinking of ways to do it
and not get caught,

18:05.419 --> 18:08.630
-and it's trickier than you think.
-Trickier? What?

18:08.714 --> 18:12.509
-Then I saw this.
-I'm not doing this with you, you mad cow!

18:12.593 --> 18:13.886
Jesus, Bibi!

18:14.887 --> 18:20.225
This house fire.
Three people died, but it was an accident.

18:20.309 --> 18:23.312
An investigation found
it was caused by a gas leak.

18:23.395 --> 18:25.147
A spark from a washing machine.

18:26.481 --> 18:27.774
Please, Eva.

18:37.117 --> 18:38.452
Look, I know what he did.

18:39.786 --> 18:42.706
-If anyone deserves to hate him--
-This isn't revenge.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.000
-I don't think even you believe that.
-It isn't.

18:45.083 --> 18:48.003
We can't just kill our brother-in-law.

18:48.086 --> 18:50.881
Bibi! Do I wish he was dead? Yeah.

18:50.964 --> 18:52.466
He is a piece of shit.

18:52.549 --> 18:58.096
But that is not how, you know--
That's not how life, society works.

18:58.680 --> 19:01.099
Okay? You can't just explode a man.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.895
It's barbaric is what it is.

19:05.521 --> 19:07.064
And you and me, we're not…

19:08.190 --> 19:09.191
Barbarians?

19:10.067 --> 19:11.235
Murderers.

19:12.778 --> 19:14.321
We're not murderers.

19:17.741 --> 19:19.117
We could do it in Wicklow.

19:19.785 --> 19:22.746
He's going there on
some stupid fucking sponsored walk soon.

19:22.829 --> 19:25.374
-I saw it in Grace's calendar.
-So?

19:25.457 --> 19:28.710
So, he will be staying at their cabin.

19:29.503 --> 19:33.257
We play happy families one last time
at Blanaid's confirmation,

19:33.340 --> 19:37.469
and then the following weekend
we blow the bloody doors off.

19:38.762 --> 19:40.722
You're talking about taking a man's life.

19:41.932 --> 19:43.058
Not a man.

19:44.685 --> 19:45.769
That man.

19:47.187 --> 19:48.313
That monster.

19:50.607 --> 19:52.901
Give me one good reason why we shouldn't.

19:55.779 --> 19:57.364
Because he's Blanaid's father.

20:17.384 --> 20:18.385
I meant to tell ya.

20:18.468 --> 20:20.637
Michael asked
if he could get a TikTok account today.

20:20.721 --> 20:23.599
Right. Which means he probably
already has one. Fucking Molly.

20:23.682 --> 20:27.477
Yeah. As long as
he doesn't rope us in to family dancing.

20:33.150 --> 20:34.276
Did you take this?

20:34.526 --> 20:36.570
-Yeah. For class.
-God, you're good, aren't you?

20:38.238 --> 20:40.407
You should take one of us and the kids

20:40.490 --> 20:43.827
wearing matching sweaters,
straddling a giant log.

21:08.435 --> 21:10.729
You know-- Just give me a minute.

21:28.080 --> 21:29.164
Fuck!

21:30.999 --> 21:33.418
Just-- I'm just going to the toilet.

